JOHANNESBURG – Gauteng Education MEC, Panyaza Lesufi says he is disgusted by the pictures of a school Principal in a compromised position with pupils in his office. “The Gauteng MEC for Education…wishes to express his disappointment and disgust on pictures making rounds involving a School Principal in a compromised position with learners in his office,” the department says in a statement. According to the statement, the teacher has since resigned. However, the Department intends to take the matter further and ask the South African Council of Educators (SACE) to strike the teacher of its roll with immediate effect. READ: Gauteng education system under siege: Lesufi “The department has a zero-tolerance stance on allegations of sexual assault and has never hesitated to act,” reads the statement. The Department has since appealed to all affected pupils, teachers, and parents to cooperate with all officials sent to the school for necessary intervention into the matter. eNCA